    console.log('Bot is ready!')
})

client.on('message', message => {
    if (message.content === '/ban') {
        const user = message.mentions.users.first();
        if (!user) {
            return message.channel.send('You need to mention someone to ban them!');
        } else {
            client.guilds.cache.get('discord-assistant').members.ban(user, reason);
            message.channel.send(`${user} has been banned!`);
        }
    } else {
        return message.channel.send('You need to use /ban command!');
    }
});
```
In this code, the client is initialized with the Discord API and the `ready` event listener is attached to the `client`. This event listener is triggered when the bot is ready and logs a message to the console saying that the bot is ready. The `message` event listener is attached to the `client` and checks if the message sent to the channel contains the `/ban` command, if so, it checks if the user mention in the message is valid, if it is, it bans that user and logs a message to the channel saying that they were banned, otherwise it logs a message to the channel saying that they need to use `/ban` command to ban someone.

